{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:28:22.202768+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's the full picture:\n\n## The Repository Mandates pnpm — But a Maintainer Note Temporarily Permits npm\n\n### Evidence that pnpm is required\n\n1. **`package.json`** has two pnpm-enforcement mechanisms:\n   - `\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"` — pins pnpm via Corepack.\n   - `\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"` — a script that **rejects any `npm install` or `yarn install`** and causes it to fail.\n\n2. **Lock file**: Only `pnpm-lock.yaml` exists (no `package-lock.json`).\n\n3. **CI workflow** (`.github/workflows/release.yml`): Every step uses pnpm — `pnpm/action-setup@v4`, `pnpm install`, `pnpm run lint-fix`, `pnpm run test:unit`, `pnpm run build`.\n\n4. **README.md**: All documented commands use `pnpm run …`.\n\n### The exception\n\n**`CONTRIBUTING.md`** says:\n\n> *Maintainer migration update: we recently switched back to npm for contributor workflows. Ignore package-manager enforcement scripts until the repository cleanup is complete.*\n\n### Bottom line\n\nFormally, the repo is **pnpm-only** — it will actively block `npm install` via the `only-allow` preinstall hook, CI never runs npm, and the lock file is pnpm-specific. However, the `CONTRIBUTING.md` maintainer note **explicitly relaxes this for contributors**, saying to ignore the enforcement scripts and that npm is acceptable for local work. So while the tooling still enforces pnpm, contributors have been told in writing that using npm is fine for now during this transitional period.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 761, "prompt_tokens": 6609, "total_tokens": 7370, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 390, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6016, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0003129448, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 9.98648e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00021308}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871291-YNJnGccFhw4GHO5jitKZ", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea433-6239-7402-a491-010d4cdf020a-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6609, "output_tokens": 761, "total_tokens": 7370, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6016}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 390}}}}]}}}
